                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-127-off662 t18290115-127-crimeloc664"></join>. My workshop was broken open; it is about half a mile from Cromer-street; the prisoner left my shop about three o'clock, on Christmas-eve, and swore he would have something of mine before it was long - I let him work in my shop, because he said he had some work to do; he had two children, and nobody would let him work - these articles had been in a secret place in my shop, and nobody but him knew where they were; the door had not been broken, but a part of the partition had.</p>
